observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Local Chief Executive instruct:
a) The officers concerned to submit a written justification on the above-noted findings and submit the appropriate documents in support thereof, if necessary;
b) All end-users to stop undertaking procurement procedures to which they are not technically and legally capacitated;
c) The Municipal Budget Officer to require appropriate documents for realignment of funds before allowing charges to the LDRRMF; and
d) The end-user to fully substantiate all transactions where goods are to be distributed to constituents by providing a complete list of recipients with a description and quantity of items/goods given/distributed.

We recommend that the Local Chief Executive require the GAD Focal Person to undertake definite activities which will:
a.) Enhance women’s access to all types of health care;
b.) Lower maternal mortality rates and provide adequate family planning services;
c.) Enhance the situation of women in the informal economy;
d.) Encourage women victims of violence to report their ordeal.

